snippet.textDisplay: Arguably, the best season of Coke Studio Pakistan so far. It was great job carried out by Strings (the producer this time). Great work by the musicians....I simply loved it.  I am a Bangladeshi - I can see Indians' remark and respect to Coke Studio Pakistan. However, there are few good Indian episodes also, where they deserves appreciations from our Pakistani friends also. Especially the episodes by Ram Sampath and A R Rehman were great. At the end of the day we all are music lovers, and sub-continent music is awesome. Cheersssss

snippet.textDisplay: Before season 7 it was mesmerizing to watch CS Pakistan videos instead of the modern day Hollywood/Bollywood foolish dancing/singing that to me is mostly disgusting show business and undermines real singing and music. CS Pakistan had revived the real singing and the musical instruments and talents from all over the world to create an orchestra under Rohail Hayaat to match the folk and sufi singing. It was just revolutionary and great achievement.
snippet.textOriginal: Before season 7 it was mesmerizing to watch CS Pakistan videos instead of the modern day Hollywood/Bollywood foolish dancing/singing that to me is mostly disgusting show business and undermines real singing and music. It was just revolutionary and great achievement.

snippet.textDisplay: Abida Parveen is amazing of course but String's creativity is so boring as compared to Rohail Hayaat.
